Russian singer Soso Pavliashvili at his concert in Beijing Photo: Yin Yeping/GTOne of Russia's best-known pop singers and composers of ethnic Georgian descent, Soso Pavliashvili, performed during his solo concert at the Russian Cultural Center in Beijing on October 16. The concert was titled "Sing with me," during which he enthralled the audience with some famous old songs. The enthusiastic audience also joined him in reverberating with his mesmerizing voice. The event started with the song "I love you, China" in the Russian language, and was followed by some of his popular works that included "The sky in the palm of your hand" and "Pray for the parents." Diplomats, representatives from media and friendly groups graced the concert and enjoyed this original Russian music feast.Â  
